52.4	Bernhard_Goetz	Bernhard Goetz	Bernhard Hugo Goetz (born November 7, 1947) is an American man best known for shooting four young black men who tried to mug him on a New York City Subway train, resulting in his conviction for illegal possession of a firearm. He came to symbolize New Yorkersâ€™ frustrations with the high crime rates of the early 1980s. The incident occurred on a No. 2 train in Manhattan on . It sparked a nationwide debate on race and crime in major cities, and the legal limits of self-defense.	
